data.title: Bill Clinton Birthplace, Hope
data.meta_description: Former President Bill Clinton was born on August 19, 1946 at Julia Chester Hospital in Hope, Arkansas. He later spent the next four years of his life at a house owned by his grandparents Edith Grisham and James Eldridge Cassidy. The house was built in 1917 and was located at 117 South Hervey Street in Hope. Dr. H. S. Garrett was the chief architect. This house was added to the National Register of Historic Places on May 19, 1994.
